    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Night Our Cable Went Dark</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Michael Pravica letter on May 2 editorial holds media giants are not interested in serving best interests of their viewers</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Blackout Battle'' (editorial, May 2): I hope that the media giants continue to slug it out. Then, we can all realize that these companies are not interested in serving the best interests of their viewers but are interested in garnering more profits.</p>
        <p>Americans watch too much television anyway. We need a break!</p>
        <p>MICHAEL PRAVICA  Las Vegas, N.M., May 2, 2000</p>
      </block>
